6	--									Patrick Lehmann
7	--
8	-- Entity:				 	True dual-port memory.
9	--
10	-- Description:
11	-- -------------------------------------
12	-- Inferring / instantiating true dual-port memory, with:
13	--
14	-- * dual clock, clock enable,
15	-- * 2 read/write ports.
16	--
17	-- Command truth table for port 1, same applies to port 2:
18	--
19	-- === === ================
20	-- ce1 we1 Command
21	-- === === ================
22	-- 0   X   No operation
23	-- 1   0   Read from memory
24	-- 1   1   Write to memory
25	-- === === ================
26	--
27	-- Both reading and writing are synchronous to the rising-edge of the clock.
28	-- Thus, when reading, the memory data will be outputted after the
29	-- clock edge, i.e, in the following clock cycle.
30	--
31	-- The generalized behavior across Altera and Xilinx FPGAs since
32	-- Stratix/Cyclone and Spartan-3/Virtex-5, respectively, is as follows:
33	--
34	-- Same-Port Read-During-Write
35	--   When writing data through port 1, the read output of the same port
36	--   (``q1``) will output the new data (``d1``, in the following clock cycle)
37	--   which is aka. "write-first behavior".
38	--
39	--   Same applies to port 2.
40	--
41	-- Mixed-Port Read-During-Write
42	--   When reading at the write address, the read value will be unknown which is
43	--   aka. "don't care behavior". This applies to all reads (at the same
44	--   address) which are issued during the write-cycle time, which starts at the
45	--   rising-edge of the write clock and (in the worst case) extends
46	--   until the next rising-edge of that write clock.
